<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 25 at 10:40AM EST  by NWS Pittsburgh</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT NORTHERN BEAVER...LAWRENCE...
WESTERN BUTLER AND NORTH CENTRAL ALLEGHENY COUNTIES...
At 1039 AM EST, an area of heavy snow was located over New Castle,
moving southeast at 15 mph.
Locations impacted include...
Cranberry, New Castle, Beaver Falls, Monaca, Economy, Ellwood City,
New Brighton, Beaver, Meridian, Zelienople, Rochester, and Slippery
Rock.
This includes the following highways...
Pennsylvania Turnpike between mile markers 1 and 30.
Interstate 79 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 77 and 108.
Interstate 376 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 14 and 38.
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads, and hindered visibility.
Slow down and allow extra time when traveling.</description>
